<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Breckinridge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-09-11"><hi rend="italic">September 11,
                                    1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 300.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 375, of the 27th ultimo, inclosing copy of your note of the same
                            date to the Russian <pb facs="0601" n="507" xml:id="pg_507"/> foreign
                            office, requesting executive clemency for five American citizens
                            convicted of illegal sealing in Russian waters.</p>
                        <p>Your note is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>